        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 21 at 5:56PM CDT until July 21 at 6:45PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>SVRAMA

The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southeastern Beaver County in the Panhandle of Oklahoma...
Northeastern Lipscomb County in the Panhandle of Texas...

* Until 645 PM CDT.

* At 556 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 4 miles east of
Slapout, or 9 miles southwest of Laverne, moving northeast at 15
mph.

HAZARD...70 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect some tree damage. Damage is likely to mobile
homes, roofs, and outbuildings. Hail damage to vehicles
is expected.

* Locations impacted include...
Follett, Darrouzett, and Slapout.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
